  "A farmer in southern Chile notices that his crops are experiencing more UV damage and sunburn during the growing season. Satellite data confirms increased UV-B levels in the region during the Antarctic ozone hole season. What agricultural adaptation might help?": "",
  "Using more nitrogen fertilizer to compensate for UV damage": "",
  "Harvesting crops only at night to avoid UV exposure": "",
  "Irrigating more frequently to block UV radiation": "",
  "Growing UV-resistant crop varieties and using shade structures during peak UV periods": "",
  "Selecting crop varieties bred for UV tolerance and providing shade protection during periods of elevated UV-B radiation are practical adaptations for farmers in regions affected by seasonal ozone thinning.": "",
  "The Kigali Amendment to the Montreal Protocol, adopted in 2016, targets the phase-down of HFCs. Why was this amendment necessary given that HFCs do not deplete ozone?": "",
  "The amendment was a symbolic gesture with no practical impact": "",
