  "Ground-level ozone is always present naturally and causes no harm": "",
  "Ozone (O₃) is the same molecule regardless of location. In the stratosphere it is beneficial because it absorbs UV radiation, but at ground level it is a harmful component of smog that irritates lungs and damages crops.": "",
  "A climate scientist notes that ozone depletion and climate change are interconnected. Some studies suggest that climate change may delay ozone recovery in certain regions. What mechanism could explain this connection?": "",
  "Global warming converts ozone into carbon dioxide": "",
  "Climate change increases CFC production": "",
  "Climate change reduces the amount of sunlight reaching the stratosphere": "",
  "Greenhouse gases warm the troposphere but cool the stratosphere, which can enhance ozone-destroying chemical reactions on polar stratospheric clouds": "",
